The new campus for Mohammed Polytechnic (VI) University, a Morrocan university that is also referred to as UM6P, has been completed after approximately 9 months of construction. The project was partly carried out by PERI, which strategically used a just-in-time approach for the supplying of an overall solution from a single source that is all-comprehensive as well as the project’s delivery. The company made use of the HANDSET Alpha Panel Formwork, the new ALPHADECK as well as the PERI UP Scaffolding solutions. SOGEA MAROC, a leading company operating in hydraulic engineering, civil engineering structures, industrial civil engineering and building, which was the project’s contractor demanded compliance with France’s safety standards. In an effort to adhere to the high demands for efficiency and safety, Peri then, made use of a total of 2,000 meters squared of ALPHADECK Slab Frameworks for the formation of the 120,000 meters squared slab area. The new campus for Mohammed Polytechnic University in Morocco was imagined and designed by the Architects Elie Mouyat and Ricardo, who are also the creators of the Casablanca Twin Center. Also Read: New Ibn Sina Hospital Construction Project in Morocco Inaugurated The new campus combines the traditional and modern elements, and it is also integrated into the “Green City” transformation project that aims and focuses to make the city a model for sustainable development. The Mohammed Polytechnic University mainly aims to promote the development of comprehension and knowledge throughout various fields through graduate studies, as well as research.